</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super">o </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">proximity s</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">ensors</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">. This includes an und</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">er-bonnet airbag to protect vulnerable road users. This has been used </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">as an aid at all static exhibits</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:14pt; text-decoration:underline">Conclusions</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:14pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">GMP </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">has</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> a specialist HGV enforcement unit which deal with the offences of </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">driver’s</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> hours, weight</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">, mechanical</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">construction</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> and use issues</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">. This includes wide loads and </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">route notification.</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">It is evident that through</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">out the operation </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">within GMP </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">that cyclists </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">stopped </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">are in the majority untrained, poorly</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> equipped with regard to lighting and visibility/ clothing </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">, slow moving and near invisible. This in essence means that </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">many</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> cyclist</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">often </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">remain</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> at the same speed of the </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">vehicles and </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">in doing so </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">continues to remain in the </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">drivers</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">blind spot</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Despite the offer of the free training from the </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">TfGM</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> there ha</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">ve</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> been only two participants </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">after the police input </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">and it is thought that this may be due to the complicated procedure </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">for </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">obtaining such training.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">From the feedback received at the conclusion of the training the participants </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">have </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">provided positive feedba</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">ck</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> highlighting that they have gained knowledge. It is fair to say that some have attended stating that the presentation is a waste of their time as they know all about cycling, and have done so for many years only to comment at the end that they are amaze</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">d at the predicaments that they have continually placed themselves in. Many thank the staff for their time. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">From our findings and comments at the training meetings t</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">he culture appears to be:</span></li></ul><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 104.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Cyclists treat red automatic traffic signals as give ways</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> It i</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">s interesting to note that if a </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">cyclist</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> does </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">stop then others behind tend</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> to follow suit.</span></li><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 104.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">A number of cyclists have informed the group that it is safer to break regulations </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">as it means that they can “Get ahead of the traffic, remain in motion therefore les</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">s effort is used to continue on their journey.”</span></li><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 104.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Cyclists do not need any lights as there is sufficient street lighting.</span></li><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 104.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Some cyclists prefer to ride solely on the footpath </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">as the roads are too dangerous (despite the footpath being full of pedestrians)</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 104.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Cyc</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">lists invariably wear dark clothing again impeding other road users from noticing them.</span></li><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 104.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Cyclists continually believe</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> that other road users should lookout for them rather than </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">that </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">they ride defensively.</span></li><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 104.11pt; padding-left:3.89pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Many felt that they </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">were</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> being persecuted and that th</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">e police should have better things to do</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> like stopping the motorists.</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-